spans.text: rolling round Thy own fair Orb without a Bound : Whether Thee thy Supplicants call Truth , or Good , or One , or All , Ei or Iao ; Thee we hail Essence that can never fail , Graecian or Barbaric Name , Thy steadfast Being still the same
Whether Thee thy Supplicants call Truth , or Good , or One , or All , Ei or Iao
Thy steadfast Being still the same
Repeating in their warbling Throats : And ere to soft Repose they go , Teach them to their Lords below : On the green Turf , their mossy Nest , The Evening Anthem swells their Breast
so swift his Race above , Mortals can't perceive him move : So smooth his Course , oblique or strait , Olympus shakes not with his Weight
smooth his Course , oblique or strait
Eiresione we'll no more , Imaginary Power
Since Oil , and Wool , and cheering Wine , And Life-sustaining Bread is thine
you immortal Woods and Groves , Which the enamoured Student loves
high in Air your Branches grow
Your leafy Arms to Heaven extend
The threatening Vengeance of the Skies
Life or Death , his Mind's at rest , Since what Thou sendest
Life or Death , his Mind's at rest , Since what Thou sendest
mount the Shades till he is gone
the Skies , Fantastic Forms the Air invade
What Shrines or Altars shall we raise To secure your Endless Praise
we Monuments supply , To rescue what can never die
Thou with Jove our Vows shalt share , Of Jove and Thee We are the Care
Shines serene on All thy Race , We thy Magnificence adore , And thy wellknown Aid implore : Nor vainly for thy Help we call ; Nor can we want : For thou art All
